Step 2.5: Start ZooKeeper
# Start ZooKeeper in background
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/zookeeper-server-start.sh -daemon $KAFKA_HOME/config/zookeeper.properties

# Wait for ZooKeeper to start
sleep 5

# Verify ZooKeeper is running
netstat -tuln | grep 2181
Step 2.6: Start All Kafka Brokers
# Start broker 1
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-server-start.sh -daemon $KAFKA_HOME/config/server-1.properties

# Wait for broker to initialize
sleep 10

# Start broker 2
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-server-start.sh -daemon $KAFKA_HOME/config/server-2.properties

# Wait for broker to initialize
sleep 10

# Start broker 3
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-server-start.sh -daemon $KAFKA_HOME/config/server-3.properties

# Wait for all brokers to initialize
sleep 10
Step 2.7: Verify All Services Are Running
# Check if all ports are listening
netstat -tuln | grep -E '2181|9092|9093|9094'

# Check running Java processes
jps

# Expected output should show:
# - QuorumPeerMain (ZooKeeper)
# - Kafka (3 instances)
Task 3: Test Cluster Functionality
Step 3.1: Create a Replicated Topic
# Create topic with 3 partitions and replication factor of 3
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-topics.sh --create \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --replication-factor 3 \
  --partitions 3 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic

# List topics
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-topics.sh --list \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
Step 3.2: Describe Topic Details
# View topic configuration and partition distribution
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-topics.sh --describe \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic
Expected Output Analysis:

Each partition should have a leader on different brokers
Replicas should be distributed across all three brokers
ISR (In-Sync Replicas) should show all replicas
Step 3.3: Test Producer
# Start console producer
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-console-producer.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic
Instructions:

Type several messages (one per line)
Example messages:
Message 1: Testing broker 1
Message 2: Testing broker 2
Message 3: Testing broker 3
Press Ctrl+C to exit
Step 3.4: Test Consumer
Open a new terminal session and run:

# Start console consumer from beginning
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic \
  --from-beginning
Verification: You should see all messages you produced earlier.

Step 3.5: Test Consumer Groups
# Start consumer with consumer group
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic \
  --group test-consumer-group \
  --from-beginning
Press Ctrl+C after viewing messages.

# List consumer groups
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
