Step 3.6: Test Cluster Resilience
# Find Kafka process IDs
jps | grep Kafka

# Stop one broker (use the PID from broker on port 9094)
kill <PID_of_broker_3>

# Wait a moment
sleep 5

# Check topic status
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-topics.sh --describe \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic
Observation: The cluster should still be operational with 2 out of 3 brokers running. Partitions previously led by broker 3 should have new leaders.

# Restart broker 3
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-server-start.sh -daemon $KAFKA_HOME/config/server-3.properties

# Wait for broker to rejoin
sleep 10

# Verify cluster is fully operational
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-topics.sh --describe \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic test-cluster-topic
